single-c fit overview

Pawel Sadlowski

single-c was fit to data preprocessed with RP method C and limited to 10 most popular items. Price shock was left unscaled.

v3b1_single model was used with k=30

Runtime ranged 3.6-3.8h and max memory use was not measured. RDS fit file measures approx. 900MB.

No sampling issues

Sampling problems

if ( het_r) {
  pairs( fit, pars = c( 'sigma_lower', 'sigma_upper', 'lp__'))
} else {
  pairs( fit, pars = c( 'r_lower', 'r_upper', 'lp__'))
}

  geom_point( aes( x = ess_tail, y = rhat, color = rhat > 1.03)) +

  xlab( 'Tail ESS') + ylab( 'Rhat')

\(\hat{R}\) problems usually coincide with low Bulk ESS, the relationship is not as clear for Tail ESS.
